        "interpretation": "Chromosomal analysis (GTG-Banding with 500 band resolution) following stimulated cell culture techniques revealed a normal female karyotype without apparent numerical and structural chromosomal abnormality or rearrangement in all the metaphases analysed at the band resolution achieved. Only 17 metaphases were available for analysis in this case. Low mitotic index precluded the standard analysis of 20 cells. Hence, low level mosaicism cannot be ruled out. Kindly note that the metaphases obtained were of suboptimal quality. A normal male has 46,XY karyotype and a normal female has 46,XX karyotype. The karyotype is designated according to International System For Human Cytogenetic Nomenclature (ISCN-2024)."
